When I 'Move' an issue and type the name of the new project (I love the typing ability, guys! -- so much easier than a list!), and then hit TAB to move to the 'Issue Type' field, the displayed Issue Type still belongs to the old Project, not the new Project.

If I pull-down the list, then I only see things for the new Project, but that the 'current' selection is the one that's out of place.

It's currently the case that when the number of users in JIRA is over 5000 the project role user picker stops working, and customer are required to add a setting in jira-config.properties as such:

{code}
jira.ajax.autocomplete.userpicker.limit=50000
{code}

The solve for this has previously be documented [here|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRAKB/Unable+to+add+users+to+a+project+role].

Customers seem to continue to get stuck on this point, it would be better that this setting is automatically adjusted in accordance to the number of users that are in the system to avoid having to put in the manual override and this issue coming up again.

