When creating a sub-task, it would make sense to auto-prefill certain fields. E.g. a sub-task with a different value in "Affected Version/s" than its parent makes no sense IMHO. Same goes for "Fix Version/s" if you use this field for both, the version when it got fixed and the version when it should get fixed (as long as it isn't resolved). By default it should also have the same Assignee as its parent, the same priority, and the same labels.

Sure, this is not always desirable for all fields to have equal values than the parent but then you can still customize any field in any way you like. I think it covers the >90% case and saves you a lot of typing work when creating sub-tasks. Having to enter everything for each sub-task, even though it's only a single field you want to be different per sub-task (other than the Summary, of course) is just a lot of unnecessary work, methinks.

