The objective is that when a new version of a project is created, a set of issues assotiated with that version is automatically created (e.g., documentation elaboration and reviewing, test specification and execution, etc). The fact that these issues must be closed before the version can be release ensures that no tasks are left behind, allowing an effective enforcement of Software Development Quality Processes.

The automatic issues to be created can be defined by the project lead (or an administrator), thus allowing JIRA to be tailored to each company's rules.

To avoid work repetition, one should be able to import automatic issues from one project to another, or to define global rules on JIRA that are inherited by all Projects. The inherited rules can then be tailored to the project's specific rules.

